Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the
boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a
board, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} or a #rolling pin{} until it's
1-2 cm thick.

Crack the @egg{1} into a medium #bowl{} and whisk. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50} into
another bowl, then season with the @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumbs and pepper.

Season the chicken, then dip it into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's
completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging
> and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the
pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before
> you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan, and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%mins}
on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf until cooked
through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from oven and set aside.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @spaghetti{180} and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{8%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir
through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%secs}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), @chicken
stock paste{10} and @sugar{1} and @water{100} for the sauce. Simmer until thickened,
~{8-10%mins}.

Once the sauce has thickened, gently stir through half the @parmigiano reggiano{40},
then remove from the heat.

Spoon a third of the tomato sauce over the crispy chicken. Top with the remaining
parmigiano.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese is bubbling and golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once cooked, add the spaghetti to the remaining tomato sauce. Add a splash of water if
it's a little thick.

Share the spaghetti between your bowls and top with the chicken parmigiana. Drizzle
over the @fresh pesto{32} to finish.

Serve the @wild rocket{20} salad alongside finished with a drizzle of the
@balsamic glaze{12}.

Enjoy!